data.name: JUMPING JACKS
description: Stand with your feet together and your hands at your sides
Jump and kick your legs out to shoulder width and bring your hands over your head
Jump and get back to starting position

data.name: PUSH-UPS
description: Place hands on the floor directly underneath your shoulder
Position your toes on the ground
Look forward and lower your chest until it's a few inches from the ground
Keep your body straight from heel to head
Exhale and push back up quickly

data.name: HIGH KNEES RUNNING IN PLACE
description: Run in place while lifting our knees as high as you can
Swing arms as if you are running normally

data.name: SQUAT THRUSTS
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides
Lower into a squat position and place your hands on the floor
Kick or step your legs back into a plank position
Jump or step your legs forward to return to a squat position. Return to the standing position
Repeat

data.name: NO ROPE JUMP ROPE
description: Stand with feet shoulder width apart, arms down and knees together and slightly bent
Contract abs and quickly push off toes, bursting up with feet and wrists flexed (like you are holding a jump rope)
Land softly on balls of feet with knees slightly bent
Don't let your knees bend too much

data.name: PLANK JACKS
description: Start in plank position with arms straight, wrists directly below shoulders, legs together. Engage abs, and jump feet out into a wide V
Hop feet back together to return to start
Continue quickly jumping in and out for 1 minute

data.name: SQUAT JUMPS
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Start by doing a regular squat, then engage your core and jump up explosively
When you land, lower your body back into the squat position
Repeat

data.name: BICYCLE CRUNCHES
description: Lie face up on on the floor and place your hands behind your head, lightly supporting it with your fingers
Bring the knees in to the chest and lift the shoulder blades off the floor without pulling on the neck
Rotate to the left, bringing the right elbow towards the left knee as you straighten the other leg
Switch sides, bringing the left elbow towards the right knee
Continue alternating sides in a "pedaling" motion

data.name: JOG IN PLACE
description: Jog in place at a brisk pace to get your heart rate up

data.name: BUTT KICKS
description: Start standing tall and bring one heel off the floor towards your glutes, the opposite hand comes up towards your shoulder like running arms
Switch to the other side

data.name: SPEED RUN IN PLACE
description: Slightly bent your knee and hips
Run as fast as you can

data.name: LATERAL HOPS
description: Keep both legs close together
Hop left and right over an imaginary line

data.name: SPEED SKATERS
description: Stand with feet together, arms by sides
Take a big step to the side and as you do, sweep your other leg behind you while bringing your arm across your body
Now repeat the motion to the other side
To make it more challenging, hop instead of step from side to side

data.name: PIGEON STRETCH (LEFT)
description: Begin in a plank position
Tighten your abdominals and pull your right knee toward your right hand placing your right foot as close to your left hand as you can
Keep your back leg long and keep your hips even as you relax your weight through the middle of your hips
Breathe and hold for 30 seconds
Step back into plank and switch sides

data.name: PIGEON STRETCH (RIGHT)
description: Begin in a plank position
Tighten your abdominals and pull your left knee toward your left hand placing your left foot as close to your right hand as you can
Keep your back leg long and keep your hips even as you relax your weight through the middle of your hips
Breathe and hold for 30 seconds
Step back into plank and switch sides

data.name: TRUNK CIRCLES
description: Stand straight with your hands rested on your waist
Keep your core stable and bend your trunk forward
Slowly rotate your trunk in a circular motion
Repeat

data.name: PLIE SQUATS
description: Stand with your feet spaced slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Point your toes very slightly outwards
Bend your knees and lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor
Hold for 1 second then move your body back up

data.name: TOE TOUCH SIDE LUNGES
description: Lower down to a regular lateral lunge on your right leg
Keep your back straight and chest high, and bring your left arm across your body to touch your right toes
Reverse the movement and return to stand
Repeat on the other side

data.name: INCHWORMS
description: Stand tall, and bend over until your fingertips are on the floor
Walk the hands forward while keeping the legs straight until you've reached a traditional push-up position
Finish off the move by taking tiny steps to get your feet back up to your hands

data.name: LUNGES (LEFT)
description: Keep your upper body straight, with your shoulders back and relaxed and chin up
Step forward with one leg, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at a 90 degree angle
Push against your heels to return back to starting position and repeat with other leg

data.name: LUNGES (RIGHT)
description: Keep your upper body straight, with your shoulders back and relaxed and chin up
Step forward with one leg, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at a 90 degree angle
Push against your heels to return back to starting position and repeat with other leg

data.name: BROAD JUMPS WITH JACKS
description: Start with feet shoulder width apart and hips slightly flexed
Descend by rapidly bending at the hips and knees, while pulling the arms back to create momentum
From the bottom position rapidly explode through the legs, extending your hips and knees and pulling your arms forward and through
Jump as far as you can, and then jump up and kick your legs out to shoulder width and bring your hands over your head
Repeat jumping jack twice and do the same process back.

data.name: BURPEES
description: Bend over or squat down and place your hands on the floor in front of you, just outside of your feet
Jump both feet back so that you're now in plank position
Drop to a push-up your chest should touch the floor and then push up to return to plank position
Jump the feet back in toward the hands
Explosively jump into the air, reaching your arms straight overhead

data.origin: SIDE LUNGE SLIDES TO SQUAT JUMP
data.name: SIDE LUNGE SLIDES TO SQUAT JUMP
description: Stand Straight and step out into a side lunge
Shift your hips to the other side onto a side lunge lunge
Jump out and repeat to the other side

data.name: FLUTTER KICK SQUATS
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and with one foot forward and the other foot behind you
Jump and switch leg positions
Jump again, landing with your feet a little wider than shoulder width apart, and squat
Jump to return to the starting position and repeat the exercise

data.name: STANDING SIDE BENDS
description: Standing tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, hold your hands together and raise your arms up and above your head
Bend your torso to the right, as far as it feels comfortable, and pause
Bend your torso to the right, as far as it feels comfortable, and pause
Return to the initial position and bend to the left side	Keep alternating sides

data.name: COBRA POSE
description: Lie facedown on the floor with your palms near your chest
Lift your torso by strengthening your arms and bending at the hips
Pull shoulders back and push chest out
Hold for the length of exercise

data.name: BACK STRETCH
description: Start on all fours, keep your arms forward and sit back so your butt is resting just above your heels
Hold and breathe deeply, feeling the breath reach all the way into your hips

data.name: STEP JACKS
description: Stand with your feet together and your hands at your sides
Take a lateral step and clap your hands above your head at the same time
Return to the starting position
Repeat

data.name: QUICK FEET IN AND OUTS
description: Start in an athletic stance with feet slightly wider than shoulder width, knees bent, hips flexed, and a neutral spine
Quickly alternate lifting your feet up and putting them down just off the ground. Go as fast as you can

data.name: BACK LUNGES WITH KNEE UPS (LEFT)
description: Take a medium-sized step back into a lunge, bending back leg so knee almost touches the ground
Push into front foot to return to standing and drive knee back up toward chest
Switch sides and repeat

data.name: BACK LUNGES WITH KNEE UPS (RIGHT)
description: Take a medium-sized step back into a lunge, bending back leg so knee almost touches the ground
Push into front foot to return to standing and drive knee back up toward chest
Switch sides and repeat

data.name: WALKING BURPEES
description: Put your hands down on the floor in front of you
Step back one leg at the time, first right, then left. You're now in plank position
Step the legs back under your chest in the same order, first right and then left
Stand up and extend your arms overhead
Repeat

data.name: TRICEP DIPS
description: Sit on floor with knees bent, feet flat
Lean torso back 45 degrees and place palms on floor under shoulders, fingers facing out
Bring left knee to chest and place left foot atop right knee
Bend elbows directly behind you and lift hips a few inches
Repeat

data.name: RUSSIAN TWISTS
description: Put your feet flat on the floor at a ninety-degree angle, and then lean back to lift your feet off the floor at about forty-five degree
Rotate your shoulders to bring the arms to move from side to side
Hands reach the ground on the two sides, eyes move following the hands

data.name: A-SKIPS
description: Keep posture upright and drive your arms forward the same as you would when running
Drive the knee up high above the hip and bring it down fast
Make sure to keep your knees high

data.name: KNEE PUSH-UPS
description: Balance on your hands and knees, your body forming a straight line from your knees to your head
Bend your elbows and lower your body to the floor, stopping just before your chest touches the ground
Press yourself back to start
You can make the exercise harder by doing a normal pushup, or easier by shifting more weight onto the knees

data.name: PLANK WITH SHOULDER TAPS
description: Come down on your hands and knees, tapping on your shoulder from one side to the other
Force yourself by keeping your abs in tight and keeping your body from swaying	Force yourself by keeping your abs in tight and keeping your body from swaying

data.name: MOUNTAIN CLIMBERS
description: Start in a push-up position
Bring one knee up to your chest
Return leg to starting position
Bring the other knee up to your chest
Repeat. Make the exercise more difficult by quickening the pace and alternating legs simultaneously

data.name: SIDE KNEE RAISES (LEFT)
description: Lean to the opposite side of the knee that you are lifting
Keep your knees coming up straight to the ceiling and then use your arm and pull

data.name: SIDE KNEE RAISES (RIGHT)
description: Lean to the opposite side of the knee that you are lifting
Keep your knees coming up straight to the ceiling and then use your arm and pull

data.name: VERTICAL LEG CRUNCHES
description: Lie on the floor and extend legs straight up
Place your hands behind your head
Contract your abs and lift your shoulder blades off the floor
Lower your shoulders and repeat. Remember to avoid pulling your head with your hands and focus on contracting the abs

data.name: SHUFFLE SQUATS
description: Start with the legs shoulder width apart, dropping down into a squat position
Sit the butt back, keeping your chest up, and abs pulled in tight (belly button to spine). Elbows bent at 90 degrees
Holding the squat position take a large side step with your right leg and begin shuffling quickly from side to side without ever crossing your feet
Stay low with chest up

data.name: HAND RELEASE PUSH-UPS
description: Get down on the ground and place your palms flat on the floor in push-up position
Bend at the elbows and lower your chest all the way to the ground
Lift both hands off the floor, place them back on the ground, and then push yourself back up

data.name: SPIDERMAN PLANK
description: Start in a plank position
Alternate bringing up your knees to your arms from the side

data.name: LATERAL HIP OPENERS
description: Be sure to keep both feet pointed straight ahead
Keep your foot of the straight leg flat on the ground
Exhale as you sit into each side
Your ankle, knee and your hip should be in-line at the bottom of each rep

data.name: FRONT LUNGES WITH TWIST
description: Stand straight with your feet hip-width apart and your arms lifted at the front
Take a step forward with your right leg, bend both knees and rotate your torso to the right
Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the left side
Repeat

data.name: MERMAIDS WITH TWIST (LEFT)
description: This one is hard to explain. Watch the video

data.name: MERMAIDS WITH TWIST (RIGHT)
description: This one is hard to explain. Watch the video

data.name: SIDE PLANK WITH KNEE CRUNCHES (LEFT)
description: Lay on your right side with forearm below shoulder, body lifted, legs straight and feet stacked
Keep body straight, abs tight and place left hand behind your ear
Bring the elbow and knee in and try to tap elbow and knee together
Pause then return to start position
Repeat

data.name: SIDE PLANK WITH KNEE CRUNCHES (RIGHT)
description: Lay on your left side with forearm below shoulder, body lifted, legs straight and feet stacked
Keep body straight, abs tight and place right hand behind your ear
Bring the elbow and knee in and try to tap elbow and knee together
Pause then return to start position
Repeat

data.name: ROCKING PLANK
description: Start in a plank position
Shift your body forward by bending at the elbows and toes
Move back to start position
Repeat

data.name: BICYCLE KICKS
description: Lie on your back and place your hands flat on the floor beside you
Bend your knees 90 degrees
Alternate straightening your legs and bringing them back to 90 degrees

data.name: PLANK WITH LEG LIFTS
description: Start in a plank position
Brace your core and lift one foot off the floor
Hold for two seconds, then lower your foot
Repeat with your other foot and keep alternating

data.name: SINGLE LEG V-UPS
description: Lie face up on the floor with your arms and legs straight
Hold your arms straight above your head
Simultaneously lift the one leg and raise your arms up and torso as if you are trying to touch your toes forming a V shape with your body
Lower your body back to the starting position and repeat movement
Repeat with the other side

data.name: V-SIT HOLD
description: Sit on the floor and put your palms on the ground next to your hips facing forward
Lift legs off the floor and straighten them as far as you can without touching the floor while leaning back
Pull your knees back towards your chest
Repeat

data.name: REVERSE CRUNCHES
description: Lie face up on a mat and place hands under your butt
Lift your legs and bend knees so that they form a 90-degree angle. Hips are still on the ground at this time
Begin exercise by raising your hips off the ground and toward your head

data.name: HIP BRIDGE HOLD
description: Lie flat on the floor with your knees bent and your arms at your side
Push through your heels to lift your butt up until your back and legs are aligned
Hold this for as long as you can

data.name: RECLINED BOUND ANGLE POSE
description: Lie faceup with soles of feet together, knees open to sides and inhale
Exhale and slowly squeeze thighs together
Inhale and slowly open knees
Repeat

data.name: POP SQUATS
description: Stand with your feet wider than your hips and feet pointed slightly out
Begin bending your knees until parallel to the floor with your back as straight as possible
Once you reach your button position begin to push through your heels and jump upwards
As you jump upwards brings both feet in towards one another so you land with your feet few inches apart, make sure to land on your toes
When you land immediately jump to return to the starting position

data.name: LAY DOWN PUSH-UPS
description: Lie on your stomach with arms out in front of you and legs straight behind, with toes pointing to the floor
Placing both hands either side of your chest, extend your arms and lift up into a push-up, resting on the balls of your feet. Lower your body slowly back to the floor
Keep your back straight during the whole time

data.name: PUSH-UPS WITH ROTATION
description: Perform a push-up, at top rotate the body into a side-plank position
With one arm on the ground and the other extended toward the ceiling
Rotate back to top of push-up position
Perform push-up and repeat rotation to opposite side

data.name: SQUATS WITH BICYCLE CRUNCHES
description: Squat until thighs are parallel to the floor
Shift weight to left foot as you rise up, lower your left elbow and raise your right knee, crunching them together on a diagonal line, engage your abs for a better workout
Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side

data.name: SIT UP JAB CROSS
description: Lie on your back with your knees bent and hip-width apart
Bend your elbows and keep your hands next to your ears
Gently pull your abdominals inward and raise your upper body off the floor
Do a jab cross at the top of the movement
Then lower slowly back down

data.name: OPPOSITE LEG ARM LIFTS
description: Start on your knees with both hands on the ground in front of you
Lift one arm and the opposite leg off the floor until both are parallel to the floor
Hold for 3 counts then get back to starting position and repeat with the other side

data.name: ALTERNATING LUNGES
description: Keep your upper body straight with your shoulders back and relaxed and chin up
Step forward with one leg, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at a 90-degree angle
Return to the starting position and repeat the move on the other side

data.name: STARFISH CRUNCHES
description: Lie on the ground with your arms and legs extended so that you're creating an "X" position on the ground
Bring one arm straight up and diagonally across your body while lifting the opposing leg, lightly touch your shin or just try to come as close as your level of flexibility will allow
Alternate back and forth for each repetition

data.name: SUPERMANS
description: Lie facedown with your legs straight and arms overhead
Contract your glutes
Slowly raise your head, chest, arms, and legs off the floor
Hold this pose for five seconds, then lower back to starting position
Repeat

data.name: LYING SPINAL TWIST STRETCH (LEFT)
description: Lying comfortably on the back and extend your arms out alongside the body in a 'T' formation
Raise your right leg up and bend it
Take left arm to right leg, bring the leg across the body to the left. Try to bring your knee all the way to the floor
Press right shoulder blade into the ground and turn your head towards right

data.name: LYING SPINAL TWIST STRETCH (RIGHT)
description: Lying comfortably on the back and extend your arms out alongside the body in a 'T' formation
Raise your left leg up and bend it
Take right arm to left leg, bring the leg across the body to the right. Try to bring your knee all the way to the floor
Press left shoulder blade into the ground and turn your head towards left

data.name: PLANK WITH OPPOSITE TOE TOUCHES
description: Get into plank position by supporting your body weight on your hands and toes
Press through your hands moving your chest toward your thighs and your heels gently toward the floor
Bring your left arm across your body to touch your right toes, then return to the plank position
Repeat the movements on the opposite side

data.name: JUMPING LUNGES
description: start standing tall with your feet staggered, your left foot slightly in front of your right
Push off the bottom of both feet into a jump, switching the position of your feet in midair, landing in a basic lunge with your right leg in front
Repeat this movement alternating which leg is in front

data.name: BIG ARM CIRCLES
description: Stand straight with your arms wide open, keep your palms to the ceiling and the elbows slightly bent
"Draw" large circles as you can in the air with your arms
After one minute reverse it for another minute

data.name: FRONT THIGH STRETCH (LEFT)
description: Kick your heel to your buttocks and grab the top of the foot with your hand
Press the foot into your  hand to accentuate the stretch
Hold onto a wall or chair if you're having trouble holding your balance
Repeat with the other side

data.name: FRONT THIGH STRETCH (RIGHT)
description: Kick your heel to your buttocks and grab the top of the foot with your hand
Press the foot into your  hand to accentuate the stretch
Hold onto a wall or chair if you're having trouble holding your balance
Repeat with the other side

data.name: WALKING HIGH KNEES
description: Stand tall with arms at your side and feet shoulder-width apart
Walk in place and raise your left knee up toward your chest as high as you can and swing your arms

data.name: DONKEY KICKS (LEFT)
description: Start on all fours with your knees under your hips and your hands under your shoulders
Keep one knee bent at 90 degrees and flex the foot as you lift the knee until it is level with the hip
Lower the leg until the knee is just below parallel to the floor
Repeat

data.name: DONKEY KICKS (RIGHT)
description: Start on all fours with your knees under your hips and your hands under your shoulders
Keep one knee bent at 90 degrees and flex the foot as you lift the knee until it is level with the hip
Lower the leg until the knee is just below parallel to the floor
Repeat

data.name: STANDING HIP CIRCLES
description: Begin standing on one leg, leaning on a wall for support if needed
Raise the unsupported knee to 90 degrees. This will be your starting position
Open the hip as far as possible, attempting to make a big circle with your knee
Perform this movement slowly for a number of repetitions, and repeat on the other side

data.name: HALF SQUATS
description: Begin with your feet about shoulder width apart
Squat downwards and unlike a regular squat you are only going to go midway down
Then stand straight and back to the beginning position
Repeat

data.name: SHOULDER STRETCH (LEFT)
description: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart
Take your left arm and raise it up and across your body so that it is reaching fully extended to the right
Use your right hand to hold onto your left upper arm and press your left arm closer to your body
Hold the position for a few seconds

data.name: SHOULDER STRETCH (RIGHT)
description: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart
Take your right arm and raise it up and across your body so that it is reaching fully extended to the left
Use your left hand to hold onto your right upper arm and press your right arm closer to your body
Hold the position for a few seconds

data.name: HIGH KICKS
description: Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart
Lift one leg as high as you can, and try to use the opposite side hand to touch your toe
Return to the starting position and repeat with the other side

data.name: SQUATS
description: Stand with your feet wider than your hips and feet pointed slightly out
Begin bending your knees until parallel to the floor with your back as straight as possible
Push back up until standing position
Repeat

data.name: SIDE LUNGES WITH CENTER JUMPS
description: Step one foot out to the side nice and wide. Bend the knee of the leg you stepped out to the side with, keeping the other leg straight, and sit your butt back to sink into the side lunge
Then drive back up off your outside foot to come back to standing
When you come back to standing, jump up toward the ceiling, reaching up overhead
Then lunge out to the other side before coming back center and jumping toward the ceiling. Keep alternating lunges

data.name: STANDING TWISTS
description: Stand together with your feet straight and shoulders wide apart
Keep your chest out and head forward
Spot your hands on each other and extend your arms in front
Rotate your torso and head to a single side
Reverse the motion to return to the starting position, and repeat on the other side

data.name: REACH AND TWISTS
description: Bring your feet a bit wider than your shoulders, bring your arms up, reach to one side and twist your hands
Pull your stomach in the whole time while keep reaching side to side
Try to reach a little bit further with your hands each time

data.name: SQUAT KICKS
description: Squat until thighs are parallel to the floor
Shift weight to left foot as you rise up and kick right leg out to the front
Return to starting position and repeat,this time kicking opposite leg out front

data.name: STANDING PIKE CRUNCHES
description: Stand with your feet hip width apart, arms pointing straight above your head
Engage your core and raise one leg and lower your arms so that your hands and foot meet at about waist level
Return to starting position and repeat the movement with the other leg. Allow your torso to bend as you lower your arms

data.name: RUNNER'S LUNGE STRETCH (LEFT)
description: Begin in a plank position with hands directly below shoulders
Step your left foot forward to the outer edge of your mat next to your left pinky finger
Relax through your hips and back, letting them sink toward the ground

data.name: RUNNER'S LUNGE STRETCH (RIGHT)
description: Begin in a plank position with hands directly below shoulders
Step your right foot forward to the outer edge of your mat next to your right pinky finger
Relax through your hips and back, letting them sink toward the ground

data.name: HIGH KNEE TWISTS
description: Stand tall with your feet shoulder width apart, make fists and place your arms bent in front of you. Engage your abs
Start running in place. Bring your knees towards your chest as high as possible while twist your torso so your knee comes up directly between your elbows
Simultaneously crunch your upper body to shorten the distance between the knee and the fists.
Twisting to the other side

data.name: STAR JUMPS
description: Start off down in a crouched position with your feet at hip width and your arms by your sides
Jump up explosively as high as you can. As soon as your feet leave the ground, open your legs out to the sides and lift your arms up and out to the sides at the same time
At the highest point of your jump, your feet and hands should represent 4 of the 5 points of a star
As you start to lower back to the ground, bring your legs and arms in, so that you land with your feet under your hips and your arms by your sides

data.name: V-UPS
description: Lie face up with arms and legs extended and resting on the floor
Keep abs tight and lift hands and feet to meet over torso
Lower your arms and legs toward the floor to complete one rep
If this variation is too difficult, bend the knees
